# Force LF line endings on scripts and SQL files.
#
# Why this matters: the repository is edited on Windows (where
# core.autocrlf=true), but Coolify's deploy server runs Linux. If
# a script gets committed with CRLF endings, the shebang becomes
# `#!/bin/bash\r` and the kernel can't find /bin/bash — which
# makes the entrypoint fail. Pinning eol=lf for these specific
# extensions guarantees the deployed copy is identical regardless
# of host OS.

*.sh    text eol=lf
*.sql   text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf

# Everything else: leave it to core.autocrlf / core.eol.
* text=auto